[Student "S"]
{You have 9 points, an invitational strength hand. With 6 \Hs you transfer partner by bidding 2\D. Partner replies 2\H.  

You have 9 points, an invitational strength hand. With 6 \Hs you transfer partner by bidding 2\D. Partner replies 2\H. 

Remember, you have invitational strength, so even with a great trump suit you bid just 3\H. Partner puts it in game at 4\H.

The contract would be 4\H played by South.

North plays 4\H. East leads the \DJ and West plays the \D9.

Loser List: \S = 2 : \H = 1 : \D = 0 : \C = 1 :: Total = 4Losers are as seen from dummy, the long-trump hand.

You might get lucky in one of the black suits, but your best hope is that East holds the \HK.

You win the first \D and play a \H to dummy's \H10, which wins the trick. You smile. Return to your hand with the other \D, then play your last \H to dummy's \HJ, which wins the trick. But this time you don't smile because West discards! East still holds \H K 9 and you have no more \Hs to lead for a finesse. Does that finish you? 

Never say die. Return to your hand with a black Ace and ruff a \D in dummy. Dummy's trumps are now \H A Q 6 and East still has \H K 9. 

Back to your hand with the other black Ace and ruff another \D in dummy. Dummy's trumps are now \H A Q and East still has \H K 9. Play any black card from dummy, then sit back and wait for your two trump tricks! 

Bad trump splits can sometimes be countered by a technique called a trump coup.

The coup is accomplished by ruffing to shorten the trump holding so you won't have to play trumps from that holding.

Pretty much like this hand.}
[Play "W"]DJ

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:J97.A5.AKJT3.AK6 KQT4.9862.54.853 A63.KQ73.Q87.J72 852.JT4.962.QT94"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2NT pass 4NT pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "f1107d8a797de91157902507f0879a4dd76f582c57068cdcd3232ce1ec1f7ffd"]
